this was definitely a first: herding sheep!!!! Not easy, but would have most definitely been impossible without Scottie hindering the sheep from running straight into the lush expansive forest. What a cool experience🤍

details

I love details🤍🪡
droplets glistening like little diamonds 🤍

life will take your breath away; in pain and in beauty

it shape-shifts through space and time, with flickers of light, of life, fluctuating, so fickle and free and wild, so beyond our reach and understanding, all we can do is watch in wonder and feel through it all…

I’ve been grieving 

There were a few life-changing blows, all at once, and in the pain was a faint, loud, booming whisper, from a sort of ancestral, wiser being (from where, I don’t know) that filled my soul with a knowing that I needed gentleness and silence. I needed to 

exist
feel
be present
and I needed to 
most of all

stop.

For the first time in my life, I stopped. I’ve been thinking of how to express what i’ve experienced the past year…which isn’t to say that i’ve got some resolved story. I mean, I made it out of the deep, thick, old growth forest of the initial shock and grief, sure, but we ain’t out of the woods. And maybe if I waited to be out in the clear before I shared again, so I can feel like some perfect warrior, I’d have to wait a lifetime. Cause baby, that’s life. It ebbs and flows on its own time. Sometimes you don’t get to wrap your stories and chapters beautifully in a bow. Sometimes you don’t get a proper goodbye. Life just happens. And that’s a lot of what i’ve been grieving. Cause god, I want to wrap it all in a bow. I want it all to be so beautiful in the end. I want a proper goodbye. I want it so, so, so bad.

I made art in my grief, and I want to share it; I want to share my journey, because I value it, like I value every journey and story and piece of art. There is beauty and meaning in the human experience. And if there’s one thing (of a many things) i’ve learned on my time away, it’s how healing and fulfilling it can be to share your story, and your art, and share in the human experience. I missed it :’) 

Thank you for being here. Not trying to wrap a bow by saying that, I really mean it. I hope you’re all well, I really really mean that. I hope you’ve been taking good care. 

🤍🤍🤍🤍🤍

the initial domino of grief 
cascaded into others
Loss of a loved one
Loss of a friend 
Of a family 
Loss of something you thought was real 
To me it was real 
It was all so real 

And it’s all too big and confusing to make any sense of it now 

and
you 
feel it all 
all at once 

oh my god 

and there are muscles in your face you never knew existed
that twitch and cry 
and every cell stings and is heavy with sadness

And you feel 
 
And you feel

suddenly I don’t recognize my surroundings 

where am i 
who am i 
life feels upside down 

the music stopped

November 

catch your breath

try to breathe 
try to make art from the madness 
and 
breathe 

in 

out 

breathe

breathe 

breathe

it helps

The paradox 

Is that while this powerful force of life came at me, like a train, out of nowhere, 

blinding

— I was simultaneously sprinting towards it (life force) with just as much speed; 
everything in me said to 
jump 
into the unknown 
now that you are free 

—

In the moment I recall feeling amazed and perplexed by and in awe of the human spirit; the ability to hold such hugely contradicting feelings at once: sheer devastation, hurt, and helplessness, and also, sheer (or even a tiny nugget of) tenacity, will, hope, zest,

life persisting

for the first time I can’t hide my pain
I can’t smile through it 
my friend brought flowers (and pie!) 
and sat with me 
and my grief and sadness
a puddle on the kitchen floor
she just sat with me 
in it 
and it was the most beautiful, simple, life giving thing

heartbreaking beauty thanks to heartbreaking heartbreak 

I love you friend

today is World Mental Health day…little reminder to check on your people if you can🤍🤍🤍 Life is hard and is filled with beauty and suffering, for all of us. And you don’t need to come with perfect answers and solutions (as i’m learning…). My friend showed me the most simple beautiful thing can be to just sit there (or call or text) and be with. Just be. You’re not alone 🤍

and now i’m somewhere in the in-between 

it’s blurry and hazy and I really don’t know 

but i’m supposed to be here, 

in the unknown 

I think

I’m turning over every rock 
like the foundation of my life depends on it
only to find none of them are solid 

sometimes you leave when the fear of staying grows larger than the fear of going

so you go 

like your life depends on it

it’s piercing and cold but the shore is coming into view
like a miracle
just keep sight of the shore
it’s new land

it isn’t the mouth of a shark

so hoist the sails 
along with my spirits
let the wind of hope 
a mirage 
a dream 
something solid? 
carry us 

it will carry us 

it will!!!

and the only way is through, 

god

but there is light at the end of this

letting go 

Of all of the stages of grief, I find this one, letting go, or acceptance, to be most difficult. It’s been hard. The death of Oliver was heartbreaking, and, it opened up the everything-I-never-grieved flood gates of my life, and every sharp, clunky thing came rushing to the surface. 

By this point I’ve gone through the dark tunnel, or the stages of grief (shock, denial, anger, depression, etc.) and now I’m nearing the end, I can see the light in front of me, and it’s time to let go. Everything in me wants to let go, except for my pinky finger, gripping for dear life to the edge of this god damned tunnel. This part of me, my pinky finger, is like a stubborn, capricious infant. Pinky and I know full well the truth, which is that the time has come to let it all go, but it’s, and I’m, holding out for one last cry. 

In the same vein, you know how most infants, soft and squishy, also tend to have an abnormally (and comedically) strong, clenched fist? (They do.) That this tiny, soft thing can hold such a stubborn-like, strong fist, is funny to observe, a silly paradox that reminds me of the humor found in the human condition. A baby with a fist is exactly how I feel now. My body is becoming soft again, I know what I must do, but my clenched fist is stubborn and grippy, and while it’s not good per se, I’m laughing, cause COME ON! Just release the fist! 

That I should have a clenched fist at all, in the face of change, which is the very essence of life, feels funny too. A clenched fist isn’t logical, or constructive, but it is human. The time has come to let it all go, but I’m holding out for one last cry. And that last cry, for all the grief, all of the love that has nowhere to go, feels vindicated, all the same. 

“Take this fist, my stubborn refusal to let go, as a token of all of the love that has nowhere to go” 

Humor and beauty can be found in retrospect...which is healing. 

And, 

Empathy for all of us baby humans, existing for the very first time, through all of these new experiences, and big emotions, which are very real and valid for us. 

And now…when the time has come…we try to…

RELEASE THE FIST!

Featuring: “Will Anybody Ever Love Me?” by Sufjan Stevens, “Happiness” by Taylor Swift, “In My Life” by The Beatles, “The Hidden River of My Life" by Sufjan Stevens, “Isn’t it a Pity” by George Harrison, “Matilda” by Harry Styles, “Lonely Richard” by Amen Dunes, and “There’s a World” by Sufjan Stevens. I’ll put a playlist up in my stories🤍 Music has been such a meaningful, beautiful, necessary part of healing and feeling seen and understood.

and you start to see hearts in funny places
and you know you’re on your way 

🤍🤍🤍🤍🤍

🤍could be good things, in the air for me and you🤍

Full circle,
life will bring you tears, in pain and in beauty 

Feel it all
Let it come
Let it go

“You must let the pain visit.
You must allow it teach you
You must not allow it overstay”— Ijeoma Umebinyuo 

Living with an open heart 
Is like living in a kaleidoscope of rainbow colors 
Bright warm yellow embrace, candy colored pink laughter and neon grassy greens
It’s wondrous 
And 
The truth of the rainbow, the real heartbreak, is that we will experience shades of pain, too
Bruises of purple and black, and blue sadness of hurt
That is the truth of the world
I don’t know that we can truly pick the colors of our lives 
Like a pack of candy, we get the purple grapes too, even if all we want is red cherry
That is the deal of the rainbow
It is how it is, how little reassuring 
Live with an open heart anyway 
Taste the rainbow of your life
Learn to know the flavors you love, and love them so fully 
Learn to decipher which flavors to simply observe, and let them go 
You do not have to ingest them all
Rejoice at the beauty of a life lived with an open heart, and try to accept the truth 

That life will bring you tears, in pain and in beauty 

<3 

Happy 2024 

May this year bring us all more tears of beauty, and joy, and laughter. (And when tears come, may we truly let the feeling visit, let it teach us, and then… try not to allow it to overstay. The last part is what I’ll be especially practicing this year. As with everything, easier said than done. Sending you so so so much love!!!)

joy 🤍🤍🤍🤍🤍

_____ 

“In spite of everything, I shall rise again; I will take up my pencil, which I have forsaken in my great discouragement, and I will go on with my drawing.” — Vincent Van Goh 

“Yes, in spite of all, 
Some shape of beauty 
moves away the pall” — John Keats 

Drawing by Saul Steinberg for the New Yorker, 1948

In the midst of this past year, there were moments of joy, too. I experienced so many beautiful shared moments with others, so many little moments of joy and respite, despite it all, and in the in-between. Even though there were moments where I felt so frozen and broken from the hurt, or like I was sinking in quick sand, stuck, not moving at all (and yet like I needed to be there???), in retrospect, so much growth and beauty happened, too. I worked new muscles (not because I wanted to, because I had to, ha). Made it out, slowwwly. Barely? And I don’t believe that everything happens for a reason (the world has way too much darkness and cruelty for that). But, i’m grateful I made it out, grateful for what I learned, and i’m so grateful for all of those moments, and the people, that helped bring lightness on my soul this past year (and in my life as I reflect on all moments, even in the past). I feel full of joy when I think of you. Thank you from the bottom of my heart for being the light🤍🤍🤍

Food for thought. Anyway I love him so much, i’m keeping him forever and that is all. -`♡´-
